						               													<description>The London Murder Mystery game has unique gameplay in that the evidence necessary to solve the crime is buried in 'dossiers'.  Each player receives a dossier.  A police inspector's report is also included with variable evidence.  This is probably the game's most notable mechanic - unlike most of this genre and vintage, this game has strong replayability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Certainly dated, a flexible vinyl phonograph record sets the scene.  Once the evidence has been presented, players make an accusation, based on establishing motive and opportunity.   A red plastic 'magnifying glass' is used to check the answer based on the evidence.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
